  "texts": [
    "This is likely due to the simplistic nature of this approach, which yielded better results only when coupled with LLM fine-tuning.Using absolute timestamps (w/ absolute tss) instead of the relative temporal relationships adopted by our Window2Text has no impact on the recognition rate, indicating that our prompting strategy provides sufficient temporal context information.An unexpected result is that removing CoT (w/o CoT) has almost no impact on the recognition rate, while its adoption is known for improving the LLM's output in many other domains [47].",
    "This may be due to the nature of the considered domain, but larger-scale experiments will be needed to confirm this insight.",
    "However, an advantage of keeping CoT in our prompt is that it improves the output interpretability.",
    "Figure 11 illustrates an instance of a window that is incorrectly classified (with the same activity) both with and without CoT.",
    "In the first case, the model offers an insight into the LLM's \"reasoning process\" that leads to the incorrect output, while in the second, it only provides the predicted label without any explanation, making it more challenging to diagnose the underlying causes of the model's mistakes."
  ],
